      • runBenchmark

        public static int runBenchmark(java.lang.String argPort,
                               java.lang.String argRepoName,
                               java.lang.String argTestDataSet,
                               java.lang.String argQueryFile,
                               java.lang.String argVersionNumber)
                        throws java.io.IOException
        This method builds the docker image, runs the container and then runs the Iguana for benchmarking the triple store.
        Parameters:
        argPort - Port number on which the triple store should run.
        argRepoName - Repository name.
        argTestDataSet - Test dataset file name.
        argQueryFile - Query file name.
        argVersionNumber - Git repository version.
        Returns:
        Status of the benchmarking process.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - If fails to rename the results file.
